Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)
Definition

A software module should have only one reason to change.

Each class, function, or module should perform one responsibility.

Bad Example
def explain_topic():
    call_llm()
    save_database()
    generate_quiz()
    update_ui()

This function is doing too many unrelated things.

Good Example
Teacher Service
    ↓
Explain Topic

Quiz Service
    ↓
Generate Quiz

Memory Service
    ↓
Save Progress

Database Service
    ↓
Store Data

Each service has one clear responsibility.

Benefits
Easier to test
Easier to maintain
Easier to extend
Easier to debug
